@11 = ~shadow ranger~
@12 = ~Shadow Ranger~
@13 = ~SHADOW RANGER : Shadow rangers are a secret sect of wanderers intimately affiliated with Shadow druids. They advocate the usage of powers of darkness and the shadows that inhabit them. They do not hesitate from resorting to Machiavellian schemes to achieve their goal. In general, they pay homage to the dark goddess, Shar and rumors say they whisper her name when they slit their target's throat in the darkness of the night. Shadow rangers are dangerous fighters who are able to call the shadows to their aid.

Advantages:

- May cast Detect illusion once per day. Gains 1 use at 1st level and an additional use every 6 levels thereafter.
- 2d level: Gains a +5% bonus to Move Silently and Hide In Shadows. Gains an additional +5% bonus at 6th, 10th, 14th, 18th, 22th, 26th, 30th, 35th and 39th levels. 
- May use Summon Greater Shade Wolf ability once per day. Gains 1 use at 10th level and an additional use every 6 levels thereafter up to 34th level.
- May use Conjure Shadows ability once per day (calls forth 3 shadows). Gains 1 use at 15th level and an additional use at 21th and 27th levels.

Disadvantages:

- Race restricted to human, elf and half-elf.
- May only use short swords, daggers, short bows, light crossbows, sticks, darts and slings.
- May not wear metal armor.
- Alignment restricted to lawful evil and neutral evil.~

